title: Hamas leader hiding in Gaza, but killing him risks hostages, officials say
description: Israeli officials say they are closing in on Yehiya Sinwar, the accused architect of the Oct. 7 attacks. Whether his death would help end the war is up for debate.

title: What to know about Palestinian Authority as government offers to resign
description: Palestinian Authority Prime Minister Mohammed Shtayyeh and the cabinet offered to resign to make way for a new technocratic government as the war in Gaza continues.

title: Hungary approves Sweden’s NATO bid, unblocking historic expansion
description: After the vote in Hungary’s parliament, Sweden is set to become NATO’s 32nd member, possibly within the week, completing an effort catalyzed by Russia’s war in Ukraine.

title: Palestinian government resigns in step toward post-Gaza war overhaul
description: The United States and Arab countries are pushing a plan for Gaza to be administered by the Palestinian Authority — an initiative not backed by the Israeli government.

title: Fans flock to ‘Saltburn’ mansion after TikTokers show the way
description: Fans of the movie are flocking to Drayton House in Northamptonshire, England. TikToker Rhian Williams urged visitors to be “good countryside citizens.”

title: Navalny aide says prisoner swap was in the works before his death
description: According to Alexei Navalny’s associate, the deal was to exchange Navalny and two imprisoned Americans for Russian agent Vadim Krasikov, imprisoned in Germany.

title: Welcome to China’s Cat Island, where lucky strays wait for a new home
description: Ginger cats, tabby cats, cow cats, calico cats — the Shanghai streets are home to them all. Now animal advocates are getting creative to curb feral populations.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Israeli delegation expected to head to Qatar for talks, Israeli media says
description: A White House official said the U.S. hopes to firm up a deal in coming days. Talks over hostages and a potential cease-fire took place in Paris last week.
